author: JJ Nattrass
title: Coronation Street spoiler: Rosie Webster looks out of place in leg-flashing mini dress as she and Sophie track down an estranged aunt
text:
(Photo: James and Eamonn Clarke) Share Get soaps   Could   
They've returned to Weatherfield from the USA bringing no end of trouble with them. 
And it looks like Rosie (Helen Flanagan) and Sophie Webster (Brooke Vincent) are set to get themselves into even more trouble as the sisters go snooping for their estranged auntie on a dodgy council estate. 
Filming new scenes for an up-coming storyline on Wednesday, the pair left the safety of Coronation Street and headed off on-location to what appeared to be a run-down estate in search of a wayward family member - who may or may not be pleased to see the two sister. Read More Ken Barlow leaves his entire family in danger as he burns Adam's ill-gotten drug money in Coronation Street Here comes trouble (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) 
Clearly having told neither of their parents, Kevin and Sally Webster, about their plan to pay their aunt a visit, the two sister look slightly out of place as they wander past run-down houses and over-flowing bins. 
While Sophie cut a casual and low-key figure, Rosie ensured that every single eye on the estate would be on her thanks to the model flaunting her tanned legs in a hot pink mini dress and silver stiletto heels. 
Not dressed for the occasion at all, Rosie can be seen looking more than a little nervous as she totters past shopping trolleys, bins and graffiti-covered walls. Read More Coronation Street boss wants Michelle and Robert to get together: ‘He hasn't put a foot wrong’ Rosie (Helen Flanagan) looked slightly out of place in her hot pink mini dress (Photo: Zenpix Ltd) The two soap stars looked to be in high spirits during their shoot, on Wednesday (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) 
But while the two sisters seem thoroughly out of place and more than a little jittery making their way through the estate, they soon stumble across the address their looking for, and a tentative Sophie steps up to a white door with her hand raised to knock on it. 
While its unclear who will be playing the Webster's estranged aunt - or what the character is even called - at present, Helen, 26, and Brooke, 24, were seen hugging and joking around with another actress in-between scenes. 
Braving the grim and cold March weather up North, the two Coronation Street favourites made sure to keep the chills at bay by wrapping up in bright red, long-line quilted jackets. Read More Joined by an army of crew and extras, the scenes looked to be part of a big new storyline for the Webster family (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) The sisters headed to a run-down estate to find an estranged aunt (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) Shooting new scenes for the show, Brooke and Helen were in full-on Webster mode for much of the day (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) The two sisters head to a rough estate but find themselves completely out of their element (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) Rosie in particular stands out, thanks to her leg-flaunting ensemble (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) Who will they find behind the door? (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) Helen was seen hugging and joking around with another actress - presumably her on-screen relative (Photo: Eamonn and James Clarke) 
Helen made sure she was toasty off camera thanks to the help of a hot beverage and a hot water bottle, which she kept wrapped tightly in her arms. 
The two sisters look set to keep up their track-record of causing problems for their parents, as they explore their family tree. 
More recently Rosie's dubious choices and Hell-raising past as a glamour girl have come back to haunt Sally (now a concilor), with the mother and daughter facing a backlash from the local press after Rosie was wolf-whistled at by builders. 
And the trouble hasn't stopped there as the gullible model was fooled into smuggling cocaine across the pond from America, resulting in Rosie and Sophie having to bury it at an allotment - only for Adam Barlow to dig it up and use it for his own quick-money schemes. Like us on Facebook
